## Guardrails

- **Never hardcode credentials.** Always use the `$KEY_ID`, `$ISSUER_ID`, and `$P8_KEY` provided by the user in chat. If not provided, ask for them.
- **No flavors.** This rule does not use `--flavor` or `--target` flags. It builds the default app configuration.
- `testflight` keyword in trigger (case-insensitive) = Mode A. No notes asked. No App Store steps.
- Without `testflight` = Mode B. Always require **at least one** locale with notes before starting. The user can provide any number of locales.
- Normalize locale aliases to Apple's `xx-XX` format (see locale parsing rules in Mode B trigger section). Convert underscores to hyphens. Use the alias table for common languages; for unknown aliases, convert `xx_YY` to `xx-YY` and pass through.
- Same notes used for both TestFlight "What to Test" AND App Store "What's New" — applied per locale.
- Steps 9 and 11 iterate over ALL locales the user provided. The step report must show one row per locale for both Step 9 and Step 11.
- Never hardcode IPA filename — always use `find build/ios/ipa -name "*.ipa" | head -1`.
- Never use shell openssl for JWT — always use Python PyJWT (ES256 only works correctly via a proper JWT library).
- Never add `fields[apps]=id` to app list URL — Apple returns 400 for field "id".
- Never add `fields[betaBuildLocalizations]=...` to localization list URLs — it can hide existing records.
- If a version exists in ANY actionable state for the same version string, reuse it — never create a duplicate.
- altool upload can take 15-20 minutes. Never kill it. Never set a timeout shorter than 25 minutes on the runner.
- App Store Connect build processing can take 10-15 minutes post-upload. Poll for 20 minutes before giving up.
- **Never** use the deprecated `POST /v1/appStoreVersionSubmissions` endpoint — it returns 403 FORBIDDEN_ERROR. Always use the `reviewSubmissions` + `reviewSubmissionItems` flow.
- **Step 13-pre** must cancel ALL blocking review submissions before creating a new one.
- **Step 13c** retry up to 3 times with 15s delay for 409 "Version is not ready yet".
- If Step 13c returns 403: the key may lack App Manager/Admin role — report this clearly.
- Always `chmod 600` the .p8 key and always delete it in the final step, even on early failure.
- Always print the Step Report at the end of every run.
- **All three frameworks produce an IPA at the end.** The upload process (Steps 3-13) is identical regardless of framework. Only Step 1 (Info.plist path) and Step 2 (build command) differ.

## Framework-specific notes

### Flutter
- Build command: `flutter build ipa` (no flavor, no target)
- IPA output: `build/ios/ipa/`
- Info.plist: `ios/Runner/Info.plist`

### React Native
- Build: two-step `xcodebuild archive` then `xcodebuild -exportArchive`
- Workspace: auto-detected from `ios/*.xcworkspace`
- Scheme: auto-detected via `xcodebuild -list`
- IPA output: `build/ios/ipa/` (set via `-exportPath`)
- Info.plist: `ios/<ProjectName>/Info.plist` (auto-detected)
- ExportOptions.plist: generated at `/tmp/ExportOptions.plist` with method `app-store-connect`

### Native Swift / Xcode
- Build: two-step `xcodebuild archive` then `xcodebuild -exportArchive`
- Workspace or project: auto-detected from root directory
- Scheme: auto-detected via `xcodebuild -list`
- IPA output: `build/ios/ipa/` (set via `-exportPath`)
- Info.plist: auto-detected via `find`
- ExportOptions.plist: same as React Native

## Scenarios handled by Steps 10/10b/13

| # | Scenario | Version state before | What happens |
|---|----------|---------------------|--------------|
| 1 | Brand new version (first time) | N/A | Step 10 creates new version -> Steps 11-13 proceed normally |
| 2 | New build, version exists, never submitted | PREPARE_FOR_SUBMISSION | Step 10 reuses -> Step 10b checks -> Steps 11-13 proceed normally |
| 3 | New build, Apple rejected the previous build | REJECTED / METADATA_REJECTED | Step 10 reuses -> Step 10b cancels UNRESOLVED_ISSUES -> Steps 11-13 clean-create |
| 4 | New build, developer removed version from review | DEVELOPER_REJECTED | Step 10 reuses -> Step 10b cancels lingering submissions -> Steps 11-13 clean-create |
| 5 | New build, previous build is currently in review | WAITING_FOR_REVIEW / IN_REVIEW | Step 10 reuses -> Step 10b cancels active submission -> Steps 11-13 clean-create |
| 6 | New build, Apple approved but not released | PENDING_DEVELOPER_RELEASE | Step 10 reuses -> Step 10b cancels submission -> Steps 11-13 clean-create |
| 7 | New build, Apple holding for OS release | PENDING_APPLE_RELEASE | Step 10 reuses -> Step 10b cancels submission -> Steps 11-13 clean-create |
| 8 | New build, draft version with stale submission | PREPARE_FOR_SUBMISSION + READY_FOR_REVIEW sub | Step 10 reuses -> Step 10b cancels stale sub -> Steps 11-13 clean-create |
| 9 | New build, waiting for export compliance | WAITING_FOR_EXPORT_COMPLIANCE | Step 10 reuses -> Step 10b cancels submission -> Steps 11-13 clean-create |
